        "body": "\nOne of the first questions that comes up when going digital is: **how much does a website cost?** The answer depends on your needs — but in this article we'll give you real ranges that apply in Indonesia in 2026, so you can budget realistically.\n\n## Cost ranges by website type\n\nNot all websites are the same. A single-page landing page is clearly different from a dashboard system with logins and a database. Here's a general overview:\n\n- **Landing page / company profile** — starting from **Rp 1M**. Great for small businesses, personal brands, or product launches. Usually takes 1–2 weeks to build.\n- **Website + CMS (self-updatable)** — **Rp 3–6M**. You can update content, articles, and products without coding.\n- **Web app / dashboard** (login, data management, reporting) — **starting from Rp 4M**, scaling up with the number of features and user roles.\n- **Custom systems / ERP** — quoted per project since it depends heavily on your business workflows.\n\nSee the breakdown of our packages on the [Pricing Plans](/harga) page for a more concrete comparison.\n\n## Factors that influence price\n\nTwo websites that look similar can have wildly different price tags. Here's why:\n\n### 1. Custom vs. template\nTemplates are cheap and fast, but limited and often look like a \"twin\" of other sites. A [custom](/layanan) website is built around your brand and needs — the investment is bigger, but the result is unique and flexible.\n\n### 2. Number and complexity of features\nA simple contact form is a different animal from a payment system, multi-language support, or WhatsApp and third-party API integrations. The more logic involved, the more effort required.\n\n### 3. Design & UX\nThoughtfully crafted design (research, prototyping, a design system) boosts conversion — and does add cost compared to a \"just get it done\" approach.\n\n### 4. SEO & performance\nA website built to be **SEO-ready** and fast (with high Core Web Vitals scores) is easier for people to find on Google. This isn't an extra cost with us — we build it that way from day one.\n\n## Why \"cheap\" isn't always a bargain\n\nA website priced at Rp 500 thousand that's slow, impossible to update, and invisible on Google is actually wasting your money. What matters isn't the lowest price — it's **value per rupiah**: does the website bring in customers, is it easy to maintain, and do you actually own the code?\n\nAt AFSS, all code and documentation belong entirely to the client — no vendor lock-in. We answer other common questions about pricing and timelines in our [FAQ](/faq).\n\n## How to get an accurate estimate\n\nAn exact figure can only be given once your needs are clear. The process is quick: tell us your business goals, we help define the scope, then we provide a proposal with transparent pricing and timeline — no hidden costs.\n\n**Ready to start?** [Get a free consultation via WhatsApp](/harga), no commitment required.\n"
